# Sidecar Model Override + Control Endpoint — Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Let the sidecar force-rewrite the `model` field of outbound inference requests to a live, atomically-updatable override, settable via a token-gated control endpoint bound to the pod IP.

**Architecture:** A new `Override` type wraps `atomic.Pointer[string]` (empty/nil = passthrough) shared by both proxy handlers. The OpenAI passthrough (`NewHandler`) only touches the body when an override is set (byte-identical otherwise). The Anthropic path patches the converted OpenAI body. A second `http.Server` (started from `main.go` on `SIDECAR_CONTROL_ADDR`) serves `POST/GET /control/model` with a constant-time bearer-token check against `SIDECAR_CONTROL_TOKEN`. The override hook is deliberately small/localized so it sits cleanly on top of the sp-21b provider rework (do NOT implement sp-21b here).

**Tech Stack:** Go stdlib (`sync/atomic`, `crypto/subtle`, `net/http`, `net/http/httputil`, `encoding/json`), `testing` + `net/http/httptest`.

## Env vars (chosen)

- `SIDECAR_CONTROL_TOKEN` — bearer secret for the control endpoint (no default; control server only starts when set).
- `SIDECAR_CONTROL_ADDR` — listen addr for the control server, e.g. `0.0.0.0:8081` / `<PodIP>:8081` (no default; control server only starts when set). Bound to the pod IP, NOT loopback, so the node can reach it.

