**Goal:** Prove, end-to-end through a real `spawnery/sidecar:dev` container, that setting the model override via the token-gated control endpoint makes the *next* inference request leaving the sidecar carry the new model id — a seamless, mid-session switch with no restart.

**Architecture:** Sidecar-focused containerized integration (option **b**). Run the real sidecar image in a container, pointed by `SIDECAR_UPSTREAM` at a test-controlled stub upstream that records each forwarded request's top-level `model`. The test plays the role of the agent (issues OpenAI `/v1/chat/completions` requests straight at the sidecar) so the assertion is deterministic. Sequence: (A) request before switch → stub records OLD (passthrough); (B) `POST /control/model` with the bearer token → 200; (C) another request whose body still names OLD → stub records NEW (override rewrote it). Skips cleanly without Docker.

