# sp-npxq.5 — e2e: multiple sessions per spawn (agent tabs + shell)

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: superpowers:subagent-driven-development (or executing-plans). Steps use `- [ ]`. SCOPE: e2e only. Work ONLY in worktree `/var/home/alepar/AleCode/spawnery/.claude/worktrees/sp-npxq-tabs` (branch `sp-npxq-tabs`). NEVER touch the main checkout `/var/home/alepar/AleCode/spawnery` — a parallel session is live there.

**Goal:** A live Playwright e2e proving one spawn hosts multiple concurrent sessions in its single container — a 2nd ACP Pump, a `shell` (mosh/tmux) tab, shared filesystem across tabs, per-surface liveness, and close-reaps-only-that-session.

**Architecture:** The existing e2e harness (web/playwright.config.ts + web/e2e/global-setup.ts) runs a REAL backend — it `go build`s `cmd/cp` + `cmd/spawnlet`, runs them, and spawns REAL Docker containers from `AGENT_IMAGE` (today `spawnery/stubagent:dev`, a distroless ECHO stub). Multi-session execs `launcher`/`tmux`/`bash` INSIDE the container (see `internal/node/sessionexec.go`), which the distroless stub lacks. So this plan adds a **deterministic, credential-free fixture image** (`stubagent` fattened with bash+tmux+launcher+acpmux+a `stub-acp` runnable) so the full multi-session test runs HERE with no model keys; it also documents the real-image/real-creds gaps that can only run in the user's env.

**Tech Stack:** Playwright 1.60 (installed, chromium present), Go (cp+spawnlet), Docker 29.4 (usable here), the sp-npxq launcher (`deploy/agent/launch`), agentcaps registry, Zustand session store + Radix tab strip (`web/src/sessions/*`).

